MBOMBELA – A 21-year-old man was hit by a motorist driving a blue BMW sedan on Ferreira Street this afternoon at approximately 16:30. According to Jurgen Kotze, general manager of EmerGmed, the man was not critically injured and has been taken to Rob Ferreira Hospital for observation. Kotze said the incident occurred when the patient crossed the pedestrian crossing on Van der Merwe Street. “The pedestrian was walking across the street when the driver of the sedan hit him, the reasons for the collision are unknown at this stage,” said Kotze. 